1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:10,150 --> 00:00:15,250
So that hag from the second floor who was always complaining about me to the building manager and hitting me with a cane, she's finally done for.

3
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:17,350
I went to check at the funeral.

4
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:18,150
In disguise.

5
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:21,290
Roubalová?

6
00:00:21,650 --> 00:00:23,850
But I ran into her on the stairs today.

7
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:25,450
Roubalová?

8
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:27,180
Rybková died, right?

9
00:00:27,180 --> 00:00:28,560
You're mixing up names again.

10
00:00:29,060 --> 00:00:30,300
Rybková didn't complain.

11
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:31,540
She sometimes brought you strudel.

12
00:00:35,350 --> 00:00:36,050
Damn.

13
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:38,350
I sneezed on her grave.

14
00:00:40,630 --> 00:00:41,170
Oh well.

15
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:43,050
I'll go wipe it off.

16
00:01:16,350 --> 00:01:17,240
See how nice she was?

17
00:01:17,650 --> 00:01:19,140
She left me a painting.

18
00:01:19,650 --> 00:01:20,750
What's weird about that?

19
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:25,550
You washed her windows, went shopping for her, walked that mangy beast of hers.

20
00:01:25,850 --> 00:01:27,550
Juklíček wasn't that bad.

21
00:01:28,550 --> 00:01:29,870
Didn't he bite you?

22
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:32,050
Yeah, but it barely hurt.

23
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:34,350
It festered for two months?

24
00:01:35,650 --> 00:01:36,850
She was still nice.

25
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:42,750
For all that she should've left you the silver cutlery, not some stupid picture.

26
00:01:43,850 --> 00:01:45,650
I'll just go take a look at it anyway.

27
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:47,750
You won't take it?

28
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,750
Better not, Mom would probably sell it on me.

29
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:52,010
Sell it?

30
00:01:52,010 --> 00:01:54,250
Did she walk that horrible dog?

31
00:01:54,650 --> 00:01:56,050
We're saving for a washing machine right now.

32
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:57,950
Yours broke?

33
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:00,650
Yeah, it's my fault, I pressed too hard on it.

34
00:02:01,550 --> 00:02:02,520
On the washing machine?

35
00:02:02,950 --> 00:02:03,850
On the washboard.

36
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:09,580
But still, take that picture.

37
00:02:09,950 --> 00:02:12,050
So you get something out of the majority minority too.

38
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:16,240
I'll be just like all the others picking over her things.

39
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:18,150
They're like vultures.

40
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:18,920
Ivo!

41
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,550
Look what I found.

42
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:24,250
Found?

43
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,600
Yeah, it was by the dumpsters.

44
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,300
The Pajers probably put it there.

45
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,980
Hey, Ivo, just rinse them off well.

46
00:02:29,980 --> 00:02:35,250
But her constant checking whether I'm sorting the recycling right is definitely something I won't miss.

47
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:37,350
Rybková died.

48
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:40,850
Pajerová is alive?

49
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:42,850
Probably.

50
00:02:43,650 --> 00:02:46,750
Damn, I threw a pickle jar into the plastics.

51
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:49,650
I better go take it out.

52
00:02:50,050 --> 00:02:53,750
Oh, Ivo, you accidentally threw out a dishcloth, so I brought it back.

53
00:02:59,970 --> 00:03:00,870
Where were we?

54
00:03:08,850 --> 00:03:10,650
Marcelka, do we happen to have a hook?

55
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:12,190
Did you throw glass into the plastics again?

56
00:03:12,770 --> 00:03:13,990
I think she's dead.

57
00:03:14,350 --> 00:03:18,050
Tomáš, you're not doing it for Pajerová, you're doing it for the planet.

58
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:19,510
Well, you're in a good mood.

59
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:20,170
You bet.

60
00:03:20,650 --> 00:03:23,450
Štefan sent me the campaign posters as samples.

61
00:03:26,550 --> 00:03:27,750
Party for All?

62
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:29,850
Well, that's quite a name.

63
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:31,350
Everyone supports them.

64
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:34,120
Everyone who matters.

65
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,800
I don't want to get mixed up in politics.

66
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,360
Nobody asked you to.

67
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:40,240
You'll just play a few concerts in their campaign T-shirt.

68
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,700
They won't win anyway.

69
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:44,880
They'll win for sure.

70
00:03:45,150 --> 00:03:47,050
They're promising people free shoes.

71
00:03:48,550 --> 00:03:50,450
And you could've had free publicity.

72
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:53,030
Ivan Mládek practically begged for the photo shoot.

73
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:55,630
And in the end he was happy they let him rhyme the slogan.

74
00:03:57,050 --> 00:03:58,750
He's still got an extra syllable in there.

75
00:03:58,850 --> 00:03:59,750
He doesn't.

76
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:06,450
Tomáš, think about it.

77
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,880
You still have a chance to get on a billboard.

78
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:15,350
Štefan says nobody can attract as many older, lonely female voters as you.

79
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:17,020
Really, nobody?

80
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:19,250
Well, the other guys already have Jakub Smolík.

81
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:20,250
Which others?

82
00:04:21,350 --> 00:04:22,290
It's a party.

83
00:04:22,550 --> 00:04:23,850
They're called The Others.

84
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:28,550
Tomáš, we can't throw away an opportunity like this.

85
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:29,760
We can't?

86
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:31,640
More people will point at me.

87
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,060
But they'll come to concerts.

88
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:33,900
Marcelka, but...

89
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,120
You reject everything.

90
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:38,420
I got you on TV, on Celebrities in Swimsuits.

91
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,360
You turned it down.

92
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,920
You could've recorded a commercial for Davidlo, didn't want to either.

93
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:46,560
You could've been the face of Kunín pharmacy, and nothing.

94
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:51,850
Do you realize you could've had your own brand of cheese?

95
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:52,440
Hm?

96
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,350
You won't listen to me at all?

97
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:58,850
Fine, I'll reconsider the cheese thing, okay?

98
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:01,950
Jirka Korn already took the cheese.

99
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:06,150
Well, surely something else will come up.

100
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:11,150
I'll go find that hook somewhere.

101
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,140
What a dog.

102
00:05:23,050 --> 00:05:26,050
That's Juklíček, back when he still had four legs.

103
00:05:27,050 --> 00:05:28,050
It fits here.

104
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,250
No it definitely doesn't.

105
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,890
You told me yourself to take it.

106
00:05:32,110 --> 00:05:33,030
Yeah, so put it somewhere.

107
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:34,490
But Mom will sell it.

108
00:05:35,050 --> 00:05:36,930
Don't worry, nobody would buy this painting.

109
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:38,450
Actually, I'd buy it.

110
00:05:39,850 --> 00:05:41,050
Let's put it under the bed.

111
00:05:41,450 --> 00:05:43,130
Ivo, it's a painting, it needs to hang.

112
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:43,850
And what do I tell Dad?

113
00:05:44,530 --> 00:05:45,210
That it's yours?

114
00:05:45,210 --> 00:05:48,650
Take it home and tell Mom it's mine.

115
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,850
Ivo, you know I faint when I have to lie.

116
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:57,050
Ivo, do we have a hook at home?

117
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,700
Please, just leave that bottle there.

118
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:01,880
You almost had me out, but then the umbrella opened up in there.

119
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:02,420
What umbrella?

120
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,320
I found it by the dumpsters.

121
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,960
I used it instead of the hook.

122
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:10,610
So we don't have a hook.

123
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:10,930
No.

124
00:06:16,350 --> 00:06:17,150
So where were we?

125
00:06:17,450 --> 00:06:19,450
Ivo, let me leave it here, please, just for a few days.

126
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:19,910
And then what?

127
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:22,050
Then I'll know how to lie, so I can go home and tell Mom I just borrowed it.

128
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:29,050
Or I'll give it to some people and say it's just for a few days but it'll be forever.

129
00:06:29,550 --> 00:06:30,650
Is that my case too?

130
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:31,550
No, just until...

131
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:34,750
I just said now, so forever.

132
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:37,280
Actually I've been practicing and I was pretty good.

133
00:06:37,450 --> 00:06:38,750
Okay, show me.

134
00:06:43,550 --> 00:06:45,050
In front of people, I can't do it.

135
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:46,710
That's really quite useless.

136
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:50,650
If you left and then came back so I couldn't hear you, then I could.

137
00:06:50,790 --> 00:06:51,770
You're going to say this to your mom?

138
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,850
Ivo, I'll get better, I'll practice.

139
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:58,150
Ivo, can you imagine what it'll be like when I can do it?

140
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:03,050
I'll walk onto a plane, say I'm a flight attendant, and fly to Egypt for free.

141
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:05,710
Or I'll go to the zoo and feed the baby elephants.

142
00:07:05,890 --> 00:07:08,270
And if anyone comes along, I'll say I have permission.

143
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:13,070
And I'll tell Kropáček you'll beat him up and she'll stop showing off to you.

144
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:16,450
Saša, I think you're idealizing lying.

145
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:36,350
When's bro coming with money for beer?

146
00:07:37,050 --> 00:07:37,950
Probably not now.

147
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,650
I don't think he's doing too well.

148
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:41,850
I saw him rummaging in a dumpster.

149
00:07:42,590 --> 00:07:43,230
Wait, wait.

150
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:45,950
I hope not on our street.

151
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:47,450
Right in front of our building.

152
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:49,150
But that's Lexa's territory.

153
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:50,370
You go through dumpsters?

154
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:50,790
Excuse me.

155
00:07:51,290 --> 00:07:51,810
Sorry?

156
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:52,930
Sounded like it.

157
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:54,890
We're pooling money for a washing machine.

158
00:07:55,150 --> 00:07:56,230
Everyone has to contribute.

159
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:58,670
Saša collects mushrooms and Lexa looks for returnable bottles.

160
00:07:58,670 --> 00:07:59,670
He chose it himself.

161
00:08:00,050 --> 00:08:02,250
If he could swim, it could've been coins from the fountain.

162
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,450
Hey, leave our bottles alone.

163
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,250
Bro was at the plastics.

164
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:07,850
That's weird.

165
00:08:09,150 --> 00:08:10,950
You can't return plastic bottles.

166
00:08:13,850 --> 00:08:15,050
Ah, there he is.

167
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:16,950
So how much?

168
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:17,690
Nothing.

169
00:08:19,050 --> 00:08:22,450
I felt awkward, Mr. Pacovský was standing there.

170
00:08:22,930 --> 00:08:24,470
You could've waited for him to leave.

171
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:26,010
He just stands there all the time.

172
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:28,570
One hand in the container, the other in his pocket, whistling.

173
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:31,550
Poor bro.

174
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:34,790
He's going through dumpsters and now his hand got stuck.

175
00:08:35,050 --> 00:08:36,250
Do you guys have a hook at home?

176
00:08:36,330 --> 00:08:36,690
No.

177
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:51,830
It's not mine.

178
00:08:55,350 --> 00:08:57,250
No, I lied to you.

179
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:57,860
Already?

180
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:58,980
I didn't hear anything.

181
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:02,280
But you weren't listening properly, I just lied so beautifully.

182
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,800
Okay, I believe you.

183
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,860
Wow, thanks, now Mom won't take it from me.

184
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:06,960
Yeah, I can see it.

185
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:10,140
She'll come home, ask what that painting is, dive under the blankets, and put on headphones.

186
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:10,920
Ivo!

187
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:13,850
I'll say it out loud now.

188
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:23,470
Good grief!

189
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:32,850
Got him, he went down.

190
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:35,380
Can you pull me out of the dumpster?

191
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:38,940
My hands got caught on that damn umbrella.

192
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,240
Did you have to yell so loud?

193
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:43,490
I'll die of embarrassment if anyone saw us.

194
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:46,630
Sorry for having the audacity to call for help.

195
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,850
That's all I'm good for to you.

196
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:49,850
Marcelka, aren't you overdoing it?

197
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:50,850
I am.

198
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:53,950
I was supposed to be your manager, Tomáš.

199
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,850
Developing your career alongside you.

200
00:09:57,650 --> 00:10:01,250
The only thing you let me do is call community centers and pull you out of the trash.

201
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:04,950
Marcelka, I'm having a terrible day.

202
00:10:05,090 --> 00:10:06,490
Can we talk about this another time?

203
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:08,230
Just listen to me.

204
00:10:08,350 --> 00:10:09,770
And I'll leave you alone.

205
00:10:13,350 --> 00:10:17,790
Is it so hard to understand that I want to decide for myself what I'll promote?

206
00:10:18,150 --> 00:10:20,850
That it feels undignified to sell out like this?

207
00:10:21,450 --> 00:10:22,550
Undignified?

208
00:10:22,850 --> 00:10:23,350
Yes.

209
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:29,950
Because standing with one hand in a dumpster pretending you're leaning on it, that's the height of dignity.

210
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:37,450
I have a dog too.

211
00:10:38,050 --> 00:10:38,950
His name is Baron and he's a bulldog.

212
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:41,950
And he can sleep in my bed.

213
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,850
I have boobs and I'm hitting on boys.

214
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:48,530
And Baron can talk and tells me fairy tales.

215
00:10:48,530 --> 00:10:49,970
And we embroider together.

216
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:52,890
Even when I can't hear myself, it just comes naturally.

217
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:54,150
Can you hear yourself?

218
00:10:54,150 --> 00:10:54,550
No!

219
00:10:56,350 --> 00:11:00,670
And when I want, wings grow on my back and I fly over Prague looking down at people.

220
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:04,250
And when someone is mean to me, I can turn them to stone.

221
00:11:04,690 --> 00:11:08,600
What's wrong?

222
00:11:09,350 --> 00:11:10,140
Did she scare you?

223
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:10,620
Too bad.

224
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,260
You were talking like you'd eaten some mushrooms.

225
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,750
Hey, look what I found by the dumpsters!

226
00:11:17,060 --> 00:11:18,420
Please, just throw it straight in the trash.

227
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:19,040
Alright.

228
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:24,500
Steaks, sweet.

229
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:29,150
Because of this.

230
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,420
What's that doing here?

231
00:11:32,450 --> 00:11:33,550
Rybková died.

232
00:11:34,650 --> 00:11:35,150
Her too?

233
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:37,120
What a day.

234
00:11:37,450 --> 00:11:38,600
When's the funeral?

235
00:11:38,650 --> 00:11:39,750
It was today.

236
00:11:40,650 --> 00:11:41,400
Boy, that was quick.

237
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:43,850
Whatever, I wouldn't have made it to two anyway.

238
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:48,950
Good God, what a day.

239
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:51,250
Hey, come on, there's steaks.

240
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,250
My God, are you pregnant?

241
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:56,650
Why would I be pregnant?

242
00:11:56,850 --> 00:11:59,300
Because you only make steaks when you're in some kind of trouble.

243
00:11:59,300 --> 00:11:59,940
Do you want one or not?

244
00:12:00,740 --> 00:12:01,960
God, what kind of day is this?

245
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:05,650
Marcela is mad at me, I get stuck in a dumpster, and what else?

246
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:07,150
There might be cholera in the building.

247
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,500
You're kidding me.

248
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:14,720
Two old ladies kicked the bucket and they buried one of them crazy fast.

249
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:15,800
Rybková died.

250
00:12:16,940 --> 00:12:17,780
Her too?

251
00:12:18,850 --> 00:12:19,850
That doesn't matter now.

252
00:12:19,850 --> 00:12:23,390
I want Iva to tell me why we're having steaks.

253
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:25,390
God, can't we just have steaks sometimes for no reason?

254
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:26,670
No, it's never for no reason.

255
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:28,990
Expect me to spill everything over the steak.

256
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:32,950
Fine, Saša wants to keep a picture at our place.

257
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:36,250
That's all?

258
00:12:37,350 --> 00:12:39,050
I was expecting something worse.

259
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:44,450
Good grief!

260
00:12:58,550 --> 00:12:59,350
It's still weird though.

261
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:01,750
Three old ladies in one day.

262
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,860
How three?

263
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:04,450
Only Rybková died just now.

264
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:06,750
Not Rybková, I'm not that lucky.

265
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,920
That harpy will be hitting me with her cane till I die.

266
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,200
Oh, so who then?

267
00:13:12,350 --> 00:13:13,150
Roubalová.

268
00:13:13,650 --> 00:13:14,350
And two more.

269
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,150
Ivuška said so.

270
00:13:18,050 --> 00:13:19,250
Rybková is alive?

271
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:22,330
Saša got excused from mushroom picking today to go to a funeral.

272
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,150
That's nonsense!

273
00:13:24,450 --> 00:13:26,650
Rybková hit me with her cane less than ten minutes ago.

274
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,040
Yeah, but Saša can't lie.

275
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:28,940
I'm not lying either.

276
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,040
I have a bruise, look.

277
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:32,750
Could it be puberty?

278
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:34,220
Already?

279
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:37,680
Hi.

280
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,280
Hi.

281
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,650
About time you showed up.

282
00:13:39,850 --> 00:13:40,950
This wasn't going to work.

283
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:41,960
What's going on?

284
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:45,520
Look, everyone's having a rough day today, but that's exactly why we should stick together.

285
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:45,760
Yeah.

286
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:51,250
So the blue hatched streets are yours and the red ones are ours.

287
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:53,440
What is this supposed to be?

288
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:56,050
Well yeah, we do have more, but we've also been at it longer.

289
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:57,510
More what?

290
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:58,310
I don't understand anything.

291
00:13:58,450 --> 00:13:59,870
And I'm not reporting it to anyone either.

292
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:01,750
But we're buddies, right?

293
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:02,280
Yeah.

294
00:14:02,850 --> 00:14:04,550
So tell me where they buy plastics.

295
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:07,560
What are you even talking about?

296
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:09,750
Bro, Lexa saw you.

297
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:12,540
My hand got stuck.

298
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:15,700
Sure, that's what I taught Lexa to say too whenever someone caught him.

299
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:19,150
I don't go through dumpsters.

300
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:20,490
Okay, okay.

301
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:22,250
But you agree on the map.

302
00:14:22,290 --> 00:14:24,530
Oh for God's sake, whatever.

303
00:14:24,610 --> 00:14:25,410
Give me a Becherovka.

304
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:28,150
Those plastics must really pay off.

305
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,050
Did she say where Iva is?

306
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,540
Why do you want her?

307
00:14:46,850 --> 00:14:49,450
She said I could come watch her do aerobics.

308
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:51,150
She's not here.

309
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,150
I saw her go inside.

310
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,080
I didn't.

311
00:14:55,090 --> 00:14:56,170
Sis, don't hold me up.

312
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,850
They put a new dumpster on Roháčova street.

313
00:14:58,350 --> 00:14:59,190
She's in the kitchen.

314
00:14:59,650 --> 00:15:04,250
Go to her.

315
00:15:10,850 --> 00:15:11,650
Are you lying?

316
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:12,440
No.

317
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:15,750
But she's not there now.

318
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:16,350
She is.

319
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:19,450
Sis, cut it out.

320
00:15:20,550 --> 00:15:21,550
I'm not your sister.

321
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:23,640
No.

322
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:25,150
I'm your brother.

323
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:28,950
I'd rather go to Roháčova.

324
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:30,750
And my name is Linda.

325
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:45,550
That wasn't bad.

326
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:57,800
Where were you?

327
00:15:58,750 --> 00:15:59,150
We were reading Pinocchio with Saša.

328
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,520
What are you doing?

329
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,150
Sorting recycling.

330
00:16:04,650 --> 00:16:07,550
Pajerová saw me at the dumpsters and went to check on it.

331
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:10,350
She found the bottle, the umbrella, and the broom in the plastics.

332
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:12,060
Broom?

333
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:13,980
I was trying to get the umbrella out.

334
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:15,000
With a broom?

335
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:16,540
Couldn't find anything better.

336
00:16:17,450 --> 00:16:20,850
Now I have to show her properly sorted waste.

337
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:22,740
Otherwise she won't give me my watch back.

338
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,550
How does she have your watch?

339
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:28,150
They fell in when Marcelka was pulling my hand out of the dumpster.

340
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:29,750
Good God, what a day.

341
00:16:29,940 --> 00:16:31,340
If you hadn't thrown that bottle in there...

342
00:16:31,340 --> 00:16:32,280
I know that now too, okay?

343
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:35,950
Hey, listen, Ivo, did you throw out that sausage dish?

344
00:16:36,060 --> 00:16:37,060
That was Ozzák.

345
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:39,950
Too bad, it was so nice.

346
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:48,650
Pajerová is coming to check how I'm sorting.

347
00:16:55,450 --> 00:17:00,640
If you must rummage through trash at home too, at least draw the curtains.

348
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:01,160
Marcelka, what...

349
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:01,360
...

350
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,150
What's going on?

351
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:06,820
The tabloids photographed you at that dumpster.

352
00:17:06,820 --> 00:17:08,140
It's coming out in the papers tomorrow.

353
00:17:09,740 --> 00:17:10,340
Great.

354
00:17:12,350 --> 00:17:13,150
Jesus Christ.

355
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:14,950
What are we going to do?

356
00:17:15,650 --> 00:17:17,250
Suddenly it's we, huh?

357
00:17:18,050 --> 00:17:22,300
Of course you want to decide everything yourself, but when you're in trouble, you call Marcelka.

358
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:22,640
Me?

359
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:25,140
I didn't call you, you came yourself.

360
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:26,680
Fine, I'll leave then.

361
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:28,350
Alright, I'm sorry.

362
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:33,650
Sign this immediately and personally deliver it to the Blesk editorial office.

363
00:17:34,210 --> 00:17:34,930
Sure, sure.

364
00:17:35,010 --> 00:17:35,570
What is it?

365
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:40,650
A sworn statement that you were pulling a child out of that dumpster.

366
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:41,090
Oh.

367
00:17:41,650 --> 00:17:42,550
And then?

368
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:44,550
They'll probably laugh at you.

369
00:17:44,650 --> 00:17:46,530
But we have to try.

370
00:17:46,530 --> 00:17:48,130
I'm going to see Štefan in the meantime.

371
00:17:48,130 --> 00:17:50,150
Maybe he'll think of something better.

372
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:51,490
Ivuška.

373
00:17:51,630 --> 00:17:51,870
Yeah.

374
00:17:52,650 --> 00:17:55,550
Could you please finish this and sort it for Pajerová?

375
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:56,870
God.

376
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:58,350
Damn.

377
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,930
What if she doesn't believe I sorted it myself?

378
00:18:00,930 --> 00:18:02,190
I'll say you did, fine.

379
00:18:03,190 --> 00:18:03,630
Good girl.

380
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,470
I found your watch at my old lady's place!

381
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:14,290
You bastard!

382
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:16,390
Oh God, Mr. Pajer, I...

383
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:23,210
I put up a warning in your shop window to keep your hands off Věra!

384
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:30,450
And don't try to sue me, I've got a disability card!

385
00:18:35,950 --> 00:18:38,700
Oh God, someone's robbing the shop!

386
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:42,850
Well good luck to them.

387
00:18:57,650 --> 00:18:58,350
My God!

388
00:19:00,550 --> 00:19:01,850
What happened here?

389
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:04,250
Don't even ask.

390
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:06,850
Did you go to Blesk?

391
00:19:07,450 --> 00:19:09,250
I should've just left it like this.

392
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,150
I faxed it to them.

393
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:12,860
They didn't even reply, did they?

394
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:18,730
I told you so.

395
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:21,360
And what about you?

396
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:21,880
Me?

397
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,980
Tomorrow I'll start calling community centers again.

398
00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:26,340
Whatever you want.

399
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:27,340
What about Štefan?

400
00:19:27,950 --> 00:19:30,150
He said I'm a fool for caring about you like this.

401
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:32,450
He won't help?

402
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:34,850
I can help you.

403
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:36,800
Fine, what should I do?

404
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:37,640
Buy swim trunks.

405
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:38,600
Absolutely not.

406
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:39,440
Suit yourself.

407
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:43,850
Maybe those bermuda shorts.

408
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:45,450
Regular swim trunks.

409
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:50,170
And the Davidlo commercial is apparently still available.

410
00:19:50,290 --> 00:19:50,910
Not Davidlo.

411
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:52,310
Who'd hear it on all the major radio stations?

412
00:19:52,410 --> 00:19:52,990
Exactly.

413
00:19:53,030 --> 00:19:54,310
And what about that awful slogan?

414
00:19:54,950 --> 00:19:56,850
Even my name with Vomitan makes you puke?

415
00:19:56,850 --> 00:19:59,190
And what bothers you about the extra syllable?

416
00:19:59,630 --> 00:20:00,750
Marcelka, please.

417
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,920
Fine, Mládek didn't do a great job on that one.

418
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:05,180
But having your full name in the slogan is advertising.

419
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:06,740
And we need advertising.

420
00:20:06,980 --> 00:20:09,240
But I'm afraid people will laugh at me.

421
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:14,350
Well, if you think that's worse than the headline "washed-up singer digs through dumpsters."

422
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:18,480
Fine then.

423
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:18,820
You!

424
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:20,740
Štefan already took care of it.

425
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,260
He outbid those hyenas at Blesk.

426
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:23,660
Really?

427
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,500
And he also said he respects you after all.

428
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,280
That you weren't afraid to turn him down.

429
00:20:29,050 --> 00:20:31,250
And he's also on different antidepressants now.

430
00:20:31,950 --> 00:20:33,850
I couldn't have survived that kind of embarrassment.

431
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,550
Thank him for me too.

432
00:20:36,650 --> 00:20:37,650
Is that all?

433
00:20:39,350 --> 00:20:40,750
Yeah, thank you too.

434
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:47,450
Do you know where the other two are?

435
00:20:48,660 --> 00:20:50,540
The ones who also died of cholera.

436
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:51,820
I only found Rybková.

437
00:20:53,450 --> 00:20:55,850
What cholera, what other two?

438
00:20:56,350 --> 00:20:57,820
Only Rybková died.

439
00:20:58,250 --> 00:20:59,350
Of a heart attack.

440
00:21:00,150 --> 00:21:00,850
Damn.

441
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:02,850
I sprinkled her grave with pepper.

442
00:21:03,990 --> 00:21:04,690
Oh well.

443
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:06,590
I'll go sweep it up.

444
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:27,750
We're here. So, look.

445
00:21:29,450 --> 00:21:30,550
You push.

446
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:32,190
You turn.

447
00:21:33,550 --> 00:21:34,350
You shake.

448
00:21:35,650 --> 00:21:37,050
How many programs does it have?

449
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,150
All of them.

450
00:21:38,550 --> 00:21:39,250
And it's new.

451
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:42,050
You're kidding.

452
00:21:44,650 --> 00:21:46,280
Sorry, I forgot.

453
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:48,000
That works on old ladies.

454
00:21:48,220 --> 00:21:49,100
Well, not on me.

455
00:21:49,460 --> 00:21:51,020
Of course, because you're not old.

456
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:51,500
For one thing.

457
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:54,850
And for another, it's electric.

458
00:21:56,550 --> 00:21:57,450
Oh right.

459
00:21:58,610 --> 00:22:00,450
They're all electric, right?

460
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:01,310
Not Saša's.

461
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:09,880
Not bad, Lexa.

462
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:10,600
Thanks, Mom.

463
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,400
They put a new dumpster on Roháčova.

464
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:15,050
And I found this.

465
00:22:20,050 --> 00:22:21,450
Saša will be thrilled.

466
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:22,650
I don't know, Mom.

467
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:24,750
I think she's gone crazy.

468
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:25,240
Really?

469
00:22:25,850 --> 00:22:27,550
Or she ate some mushrooms.

470
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:28,140
Saša?

471
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:28,380
Yeah.

472
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:41,080
See?

473
00:22:42,850 --> 00:22:46,150
Well, I did worse things during puberty.

474
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:48,050
Help me take it down.

475
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:53,250
I mean take it off her.

476
00:22:56,450 --> 00:22:57,150
God, that scared me.

477
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:03,750
Try putting it over there.

478
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:11,970
Saša, dear, wake up.

479
00:23:12,150 --> 00:23:14,650
Mommy, please, don't sell it.

480
00:23:15,450 --> 00:23:16,050
Sell it?

481
00:23:16,450 --> 00:23:19,150
Nobody would buy this horror, would they?

482
00:23:19,150 --> 00:23:19,710
This?

483
00:23:22,850 --> 00:23:26,050
My mom hung something like this above my bed when I was little.

484
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,360
Did you have a dog?

485
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:31,650
No, it was a rabies prevention poster, but the little doggy had exactly the same expression.

486
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:34,250
I'd keep it.

487
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:38,590
Strange puberty.

488
00:23:39,150 --> 00:23:43,750
Calm down, run upstairs for a hammer and nails before your brother's arms fall off.

489
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:44,650
Thanks, Mom.

490
00:23:47,150 --> 00:23:47,920
What about me?

491
00:23:48,550 --> 00:23:50,160
You want a hug too?

492
00:23:50,450 --> 00:23:52,220
Do you know how much work this was?

493
00:23:52,550 --> 00:23:54,680
I carried it on my back.

494
00:23:55,050 --> 00:23:56,250
This is a back?

495
00:23:56,790 --> 00:23:57,350
No.

496
00:23:58,350 --> 00:23:59,950
My back.

497
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:02,650
Fine, take the bottles then.

498
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:11,450
At least something.

499
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:12,370
Bye.

500
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:14,990
Goodbye.
